  <prompt>
    Add `UpdateUploadedFilesAsync(string sessionId, IReadOnlyList&lt;ChatSessionFile&gt; enrichedFiles, CancellationToken ct)` method to `SessionPersistenceService`. Per architecture §6.1 + §7.1: writes enriched `ChatSessionFile` records to Redis hot-tier + Cosmos warm-tier with the same write-through pattern as existing `SaveSessionAsync` / `SaveTabsAsync`. Uses ETag for optimistic concurrency.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in `SessionPersistenceService` patterns + Redis/Cosmos write-through.</role>

  <goal>
    `SessionPersistenceService` has new public method `UpdateUploadedFilesAsync` that:
    - Reads current `ChatSession` from Redis (fallback Cosmos cold)
    - Replaces `UploadedFiles` collection with new enriched list (or merges by `FileId` if upserting individual files — choose per existing service's write-pattern conventions)
    - Writes back to Redis (24h sliding TTL) + Cosmos (90d TTL) with ETag
    - Logs sessionId, file count, durationMs only (tier-1 safe)
    - Throws / surfaces conflict on ETag mismatch
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture §6.1 (Upload pipeline) — the orchestrator (066) invokes this method after parallel enrichment completes. Per architecture §11.2 — same write-through pattern as `SaveTabsAsync` (R6 task 051 precedent). The method is the final step of the upload pipeline; task 074 instruments its telemetry.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionPersistenceService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Chat/ChatSession.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Chat/ChatSessionFile.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">SessionPersistenceService is in `Services/Ai/Sessions/` — within AI module.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Tier-1 logging only: sessionId, fileCount, durationMs. NEVER log per-file summary text, content, classification text.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture §6.1">Write-through pattern: Redis hot + Cosmos warm. Use existing ETag pattern from peer methods.</constraint>
    <constraint source="architecture §11.2">Follow R6 task 051 `SaveTabsAsync` write-through precedent — do NOT introduce new container or new doc-type.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task publish-size measurement.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Test update obligation — extend `SessionPersistenceServiceTests.cs` to cover the new method's roundtrip + ETag conflict path.</constraint>
  </constraints>

