  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `SessionPersistenceService.cs` end-to-end. Identify the write-through pattern, ETag handling, peer methods (`SaveSessionAsync`, `SaveTabsAsync` precedent).</step>
    <step order="2">Add `UpdateUploadedFilesAsync` to the interface (`ISessionPersistenceService`) + implement.</step>
    <step order="3">Implementation:
      - Read session from Redis; fallback Cosmos
      - Merge / replace `UploadedFiles` collection per service's convention
      - Write back Redis (24h sliding) + Cosmos (90d, ETag check)
      - Log tier-1 fields only
      - Surface ETag conflict (per existing pattern — likely throws `CosmosException` or returns a Result type)</step>
    <step order="4">Add interface method (if interface exists).</step>
    <step order="5">Extend unit tests: roundtrip, ETag conflict, tier-1 log assertion (verify NO summary text in log output via test capture).</step>
    <step order="6">Run `dotnet build` + `dotnet test`.</step>
    <step order="7">Measure BFF publish size.</step>
    <step order="8">code-review + adr-check.</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 072 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

